caption: They cancelled my order two hours in :( I hungry :( not nice :(

I went to Misi for a friends birthday dinner and we made reservations about 30min before arriving. The staff was incredible and the food was even better! Don’t fill yourself up on the bread unless you’re trying to take food home for leftovers:)

Occhi pasta dish is spectacular. One of the most delicious I've tried. Olive oil gelato is also quite special. Everything is consistently great. Smallish portions and med-high prices make it not the best value in town but certainly worth an occasional visit.

Superb dining experience, great variety of pastas with all sorts of inventive sauces. Awesome flavorful cooked veggie sides to help balance out the rich pasta. The fennel pollen steak was amazing with the inventive use of the fennel pollen.

Starters are tasty and creative, but definitely not Italian. The main dishes are small and quite overpriced, and once again, can’t be labelled as Italian. Lastly, getting a cold bottle of Nero d’Avola confirmed my suspicions around this spot.. There’s a lot more Italian restaurants in NYC actually serving Italian food. The two stars are only for the staff, polite and friendly!

Good food, friendly staff! We went pretty much just for the whipped ricotta crostini only to be told it wasn't on the menu that night :( we were sat just at the end of the desk where staff take reservations, wasn't the nicest area and was kind of cold as you were direct from the doorway. The starters were really great, highly recommend the leeks! The mains were good but overpriced for what they are and the size. Was happy to see Nero D'Avola on the menu but for $70 the bottle should not come cold... In my opinion, Lilia is x 10000 more better and worth the money! If you do go to Lilia or Misi - get the olive oil gelato!
10/10 would die for these butter beans
Never disappoints. Delicious butter beans, ricotta toast, and melt in your mouth tortellini.

One of our favorites & Missy Robbins is seemingly always on site and always takes time to greet guests.  Stellar menu & wonderful team - we just love having this as our local go to.   Solid performer / we’d cross the bridge for it any day.

The only way to describe this place is....meh. Of the three dishes we ordered only one was mildly interesting. Absolutely not worthy of the month in advance reservation we made. At least the price was reasonable. The interior and ambiance was try hard modern chic with a dash idgaf about the details.
In my top 3 in NYC! Innovative, high quality, great service. The appetizers are fantastic, I would try them all:)
Excellent takeout option makes this amazing Italian restaurant accessible. Looking forward to dining there in person.
It took me 2 years to have a reservation but it was worth it!! Love this restaurant, the chef is amazing. If you did not have reservation yet, please keep trying!!!
Such amazing service and pasta is to die for! Highly recommend! ❤

Even 18months later annoyed about this restaurant. The food was mostly OK & decor nice. But it was too drowned in oil which ruined it. The worst thing was that every time we expressed an issue to the waitress (the food is oily / we've run out of water/ could we have some black pepper) we were greeted by her responding "uh-huh" which was lacklustre, disinterested & rude.

I received a delivery as a gift but unfortunately it came with no labels or instructions beyond the pasta/pesto combo and the steak being labeled Bistecca. When I opened the steak it was marinated in evoo (?) and Rosemary. Unclear if it’s salted, no one answers the phone, texts, or dms. As a chef I find this really sub par for items that I’m sure were quite expensive. Also unclear are the 2 jars that arrived and 2 lemons, not sure what they’re for. Originally after I emailed I got a response via text explaining to “slice the bread for the ricotta...and grill the steak”. Did not address what the items were that were delivered (problematic from a food allergy perspective). Just a fail from start to finish and if you’re deciding whether this is worth it: no. *Addendum: steak was fine, needed salt, I would really recommend literature for the consumer re: the product being delivered. the number that texted said they would follow up with me the next day but never did. We cooked the pasta last night and it was sort of mealy and broke really easily, again doubly do not rec splurging on this.

Delicate pastas, and delightful appetizers that are veg centric. Long wait? check out domino park across the street for gleaming waterfront views. Must try: charred peppers and ricotta crostini, brown butter tortelli

Our first time at Misi was definitely worth 5 stars. We had high hopes because of our LILIA experience. We are foodies w/ very trained palettes. What we “devoured”: Antipasti - the chanterelles are a hit & the beautiful squash with those delectable seasoned breadcrumbs (mmmmm). Gnocchi w/ pork  & Spaghetti w/ braised lamb (Also yum & of course the handmade pastas were cooked perfectly al dente- the sauces were just enough for the pastas.) Drinks- Rose (dry & light) & the “Marcaeleone” (not super sweet but crisp- great pairing with the gnocchi). The A&T Spritz. All greatly paired with great service & proper COVID-19 practices. Cheers! *women-owned business*
Ambiance and service was great. The food... was underwhelming. Nothing wowed me, it was just fancy pasta that didn't taste amazing
Very chic, hard to get reservations. Log on to resy at 10 am EST!

I had high hopes to visit this place. Unfortunately, i tried contacting this restaurant through social media and by phone and got no response. I understand the pandemic has been challenging for restaurants but my simple inquiry was ignored.

Pretentious and overpriced restaurant. The problem with the food is that they mix ingredients that have nothing to do with the dish. I have to give a second star because the place is aesthetically appealing and service is decent.

Great homemade pasta, but sauces don't really hit the spot. Best spicy roasted whole eggplant dish (easy to make at home too). Money wine list, for good and bad. Good, clean venue, but a bit cold in style, as is the service. Too pricey and doesn't live up to its awards and reputation.
I really Misi eating here!! ❤️❤️❤️
Delicious & gourmet! Snag a reservation if you can!!!
Great place for a date or meeting! The food and atmosphere are fantastic.

Delicious, delicious pasta. My girlfriend and I order 3 aopatizers, 3 pastas, and 3 deserts every time we go which we are told is a lot. Most people can get by with 1 less app and 1 less desert.  The secret superstars of this menu are the RUNNER BEANS. Do yourself a favor and add them to your order next time you go. We try to save this place for special occasions, but we can't seem to stay away for more than a few weeks at a time.  To get a reservation log onto rezzy promptly at 10:00 AM 30 days prior to your intended dining day. Sometimes you can join the wait-list and get a table but I personally have not had much luck with this.
Loved it ❤️ Great pasta!!
Get the ricotta toasts. You will not regret it! All cocktails are amazing as well. You really can’t go wrong with what you order.
Very precise and flavorful food! Service was also meticulous and professional. Very recommended!
No gluten-free options except for a salad and a steak for two. Otherwise would be eating here at least once a week! :)
The food and service was amazing. Great comfortable environment!
Coming back on our next visit. Loved it.
The food was very good, but the portions were smaller than I am used to.
pretty but food comes out way too slow
This place is an insult to real Italian food, freshly made pastas combined with the saltiest most unpalatable sauces,
Some of the best Italian in the city. The artichokes and the ricotta toast are must-try appetizers. Excellent pastas & gelatos, too.

Misi is a very nice restaurant with glamour interior designs a nice location and bad food. from an Italian stand point some of the dishes were just inedible. the strangozzi, pork sugo, or "STRINGOZZI" misspelt on the menu is some minced pork cooked in tomato sauce, no other ingrediets no depth of flavor, nothing. a very salty sauce chucked on some pasta. i'm going to skip the malloreddus because otherwise my review gets censored. the artichokes and the occhi were good. overall way overpriced and overrated, 2 stars because the waitress was very nice.
Amazing pasta with a "everything looks great" hard to choose menu... which is a great problem to have
Misi is a one minute walk from my apartment, I don't think I'll ever move. Absolutely love the food here, what an amazing dinner. Been here twice, dreamt about it 20x. Planning to come back often.
For all the hype, my experience fell well below my expectations. The food was overly salted and service poorly coordinated/timed.
The pasta is fresh!
Good food

This is my favorite spot in Williamsburg, the food is incredible but beyond that the service is impeccable! The manager is so thoughtful and helpful, I cannot recommend this place enough. Go immediately!!
Food and ambiance was great
Get the brown butter pasta and a bottle of Italian wine! Don’t skip on veggies either.
One of the best italian restaurant I’ve ever been. Quality of the dishes is amazing. Highly recommended
Missy outdid herself AGAIN. Amazing pasta. Super flavors on all dishes. That girl has got it. RUN
The food is fantastic, even the veggies. The service friendly.  The location a little off the beaten path.
Everything was a perfect balance of ingredients.... even the old fashion cocktail. If you want a great experience bite after bite.... Run, don't walk there.

Food was overall good but service was deeply disappointing. One of our pasta dishes came out very spicy although nothing in the menu indicated so. After waiting over 15 min for a replacement we gave up and canceled it. As a result one of our party actually never got dinner and the rest of us ate cold food, waiting for a pasta that never came. Even worse, we had to make a pizza stop on our way back home...

This restaurant mixes flavors and spices extremely well. Everything was interesting and delicious, but also not too interesting to the point where it's trying too hard. The beets were incredible.  Wine was nice. Waitress was fun and knowledgeable. Only ding is that you need a reservation, and even then you may wait on a weekend. Would recommend and would go back.

Amazing place with awesome food and very friendly staff. We ordered whipped ricotta crostini, spinach tortellini in lemon butter sauce, ragotini in classic red sauce with garlic and basil and orange in vanilla bean monthly special gelato. Everything was vegetarian and absolutely delicious.
Amazing tasty food , you could feel the freshness in it to be honest highly recommended
Great experience! The food and the staff are amazing. Totally recommended!
Worth the wait for great pasta!
Delicious food. Good portions. Not huge but good enough

Good pasta. Mainly vegetarian options. No secondi. Service was amazing which is why i gave them three stars, from check in to our waitress service was impeccable. The pasta dishes were simple and tasty but to mention they were something I could make at home. Overall good date spot but not a regular place since the reservation and prices are a little too much.
Amazing service, delicious food. All the ticks in the box.

Overall a mediocre dining experience.  Vegetables were good, rustic and simply prepared. The trouble was with the pasta. Both pastas ordered were extremely over salted to a point where your face cringes when you take a bite. We only ate half of the dishes and drank two glasses of water each.  Disappointing...

This is a place that I wanted to go since it opened and did no had a chance. I finally get the chance to go and have to say it is worth it. You do not have as many options as at Lilia (the chef fanciest restaurant) but the options that you are all great. Some of the the best pasta you can have in New York. The way they use ricotta is just great. I just would like to options of dessert instead of just ice cream as now.
Pasta is delicious and challenging. Front of house haughty and and unflexible. Really uncalled for. They should call Danny Meyer for hospitality lessons.

Delicious, modern Italian food in Williamsburg. Came for lunch and was able to walk right in and eat at the bar as a party of 1. The food was fantastic. The ricotta toast starter should not be missed, although the portion is a bit big for one person. Pasta was great, cocktails were great, and olive oil gelato was delicious. The staff was also super friendly. Can't wait to come back!
Every dish is amazing. Well worth the effort to get a reservation.

It was good but I don’t understand all the ruckus about this place. Prices were fine for us. But everything slightly underwhelming. No one at our table finished a single dish. That’s saying something.
Loved it!
Great service and excellent food

There was a bit of a wait so definitely get there early even if you make reservations. I think the table seats best were because of space and comfortably even though the website says bar seats are the "best seats in the house". Food was amazing, small portions though so I ordered 3 dishes with 2 appetizers for me and my girlfriend.
Ricotta for days!
Food is great! Wait staff.... Not so much
Refused to give ragatoni instead of fetucini even though they had both.
Can’t go wrong. Super delicious food and great ambiance.

Extremely disappointed. We made reservations weeks ago and watched YouTube videos of the pasta and couldn’t wait to try it. The interior is beautiful, modern and simple. The ingredients are fresh and you can watch employees make fresh pasta. We had two appetizers and two pastas. None of them were very tasty. It smelled great but the food was either too salty or had no flavor. Very bland! Please add some real flavors to your dishes. Not recommending this place.
Beautiful, clean space and the dishes we ordered were good. Not the best pasta option in the neighborhood but good enough that I’d go again.
Wow!! Great food and service!
Such bang, bang, every time

Doesn’t worth the money!!!! It was supposed to be an Italian restaurant with authentic dishes instead we got a super salty pasta that wasn’t even tasty.There are a lot of other places where you could try Italian cuisine but not this one !!

Excellent service and atmosphere.  Great meal portions sized to share.  All dishes were relatively simple with expected flavors-- no mysteries here.  Pasta super generic in texture and flavor, though notably undercooked.  Ricotta whip photographs well.  Expensive for the value.
Sit at the kitchen bar if you can. It's fascinating being able to watch the chefs in their element. Order the ricotta occhi with bottarga and lemon! Making a second trip next week just for this.

You will get your money's worth here. Not only is the food delicious but the portions are huge. We had whipped ricotta to start and it was a huge appetizer. All the pasta is fresh and you can taste. Great selection of wine and cocktails really round out the meal.
Great food and ambience, but their entire mechanism to book a table on weekdays vs weekends, and through email, and the phone that no one answers, just ruined our experience
The pasta here is super serious.
Delicious food. Nice place with good service.

Very forward gelato. Whatever flavor you choose, the flavor will be aggressively in your face, in a good way. Mint chocolate chip had a lovely mint base with very thin shards of chocolate that added a nice crunch.
Brunch is amazing, a must in the area.
Great atmosphere. The employees are great.
Absolutely stunning pasta- so simple and elegant. Be sure to book beforehand.
Great food and managed well

This is a very spacious and accommodating restaurant. The staff are all extremely well-trained and very attentive.  The ambience is excellent. The restaurant is a bit pricey considering that all of their main courses are pasta and all of the main courses are over 20+ dollars. That said, the food is quite good. My only criticism would be that the pasta is so well made and so fresh that it is a crime to cover it with heavy sauces which they seem to specialize in. Other than that, the appetizer selection is extensive and the wine list is good

The space is light filled and beautiful, and the food is even better. Highly recommend sitting at the bar so you can watch the process and masterpieces being made in the open kitchen. Also highly recommend the ricotta crostini/shishito pepper starter (share it because it’s filling and rich but incredible), the whole roasted eggplant if you’re with a group to share (the chili oil on it is a divine touch), and the CORZETTI pasta (so light and unique and has the perfect blend of summer herbs worked in). Grab a reservation at a lunch hour when it’s a little easier to get a spot and you can experience all the natural light the space gets.

A restaurant so wonderful that if more people find out about this gem I'll never be able to get a seat ,the staff is incredible and its apparent the moment you walk in the door whomever put this restaurant together is a genius I've so rarely seen a staff so dedicated and professional as this place now the food  short and amazing (maybe 30/40 food choices) I would love to order each item on there menu the food was delicious and I have to repeat your server will also enhance your experience I love this restaurant you made a huge fan out of me and probably anyone else who walks in the door
Food is fine, but lacks excitement, especially for the price point.

Honestly was not impressed at all. There are a dozen NYC restaurants with far superior pasta (and sauces). Service was very poor, they kept forgetting about us. We sat at the chefs counter and the chef & staff were socializing with a group of 2, seated next to us, and continued to ignore us. 45 minutes between salad course and pasta course!

I went for the first time tonight, what a nice experience! Food was excellent, I was seating at the bar and the blonde bar lady was very knowledgeable about both the food and the wine! Will be back for sure! Highly recommended!
Great alpine amaro, artichoke, and pasta
(Translated by Google) Primitivo and Pasta name name name  (Original) Primitivo and Pasta nom nom nom
Service excellent..food devine..and homemade gelato stole my heart..Best birthday dinner every ..A+++++++
Omg food is delicious

Beautiful restaurant, professional, attentive & friendly staff and food out of this world! Everything was fresh and delicious, each dish was a masterpiece - from the appetizer to dessert. Thank you for everything!

We got a reservation at the kitchen counter - plenty of space and fun seeing all the action in the kitchen.  If you are vegetarian, or looking for meal light on meat Misi is a great option. Was two of us at dinner and was recommended to get two antipasti and three pastas.  Crostini and peppers - crostini was good, peppers not so much  Runner beans - big serving and tasted great.  Fettuccine -  light, with right amount of cheese and pepper  Strangozzi - this was the best pasta, and al dente. Was a little on the salty side, but really enjoyed the sauce and the pasta  Linguine - would probably put this as third on the list. Again, a little on the salty side and parsley was good part of this pasta.  Given the serving sizing you likely won’t be hungry, but don’t skip the gelato. Was delicious and wish we could have tried e other flavors too  If you like pasta, come here. Service is helpful and quick, serving sizes are large.
Fabulous dining. Highly recommend both the Olive Oil and the Pistacchio Gelato. Best yet on our visit from Perth Western Australia.

The service and the quality, flavor of the food has spoiled me for any other restaurant! My daughters and Son in law took me there for my birthday and all I can say was a flavor expoltion that was second to none.  Also the service was 5 star!!  It will be my go to when I visit NYC everytime!!  Thank you Misi!!
Unbelievably great pasta. And the veggies are spectacular as well.

Great service and recommendations from the staff. If you're here for lunch, get the runner beans if you're also a fan of garlic. Pasta is all made in house and you can tell the staff  take pride in what they make.
Really aewsome Food. Great Austrian Wines. Phantastic.
👍🏻 fantastic!
Hip and refined Williamsburg gem.  Extraordinary and exquisite pasta dishes. Every mouthful packs an intenseness of flavor that is unmatched in the city.
Some of the best pastas I’ve had!

(Translated by Google) The atmosphere is neat and nice, but I hoped the noodles were cooked a bit. Most were friendly but one female server was quite unfriendly.  (Original) 분위기는 깔끔하고 좋은데 면이 조금 더 익어서 나왔으면 좋았을거 같다. 대부분이 친절했지만 한 여자서버가 상당히 불친절.
Very delicious peppers with ricotta on bread and some gelato here

Good pasta, not the best in town but worth visiting - food is generally cooked well, sauce can be heavy (salty); good sized portions. Open, eye-pleasing environment. Runner bean app was delicious - meaty beans with garlicky sauce. Rigatoni pomodoro, mandilli and occhi had great texture and flavor, if a bit heavy. Malloreddas were ok... can skip. Olive oil gelato delicious... bar selections were solid; wines and cocktails.

Absolutely horrible experience from start to finish. We are arrived five minutes early and were very snottily told that they couldn’t help us with anything because they were still preparing the restaurant to be opened. Then why have the door open? Another couple came in at one minute before the official opening and they too were scolded. We were seated and the waiter was very snotty right from the start and especially so when I was speaking with him about the wine list and trying to understand what the different wines were as I am not terribly familiar with Italian wines. He kept steering me towards wines that were in excess of $125 Per bottle and was clearly quite disgusted when I ordered a $60 bottle of wine. We ordered two appetizers to share between three women and I have to say they were very good. The three meals we ordered were disappointingly small and mine in particular was tasteless. I asked if I could have some salt and cheese for my pasta. Salt was provided but they refused to provide me cheese. The reason is that they said the meal was intended to be non-dairy. When I said that that had not been specified on the menu the waiter’s response was: well neither did it say you were allowed to add cheese. It was unbelievable. He would not deal any further with it and had a manager come over. It took 10 minutes for the manager to come over and of course my food was cold at that point. When I asked her about it she said it was not possible because the kitchen intended that to be a non-dairy meal. When I explained that I would’ve expected that to be explained to me at the beginning she just shrugged her shoulders and said she was sorry but there was nothing she could do.  The meals that my two friends had were disappointingly small and while one was quite tasty the other was also very flavorless. All in all an outrageous and presumptuous set of behaviors. Never would I go there again and I will do everything I can to make sure people know what a terrible experience this was. And they should also be aware that my two friends are from Finland and will be sure to share this experience with their finish friends as they travel to New York City. What a terrible way to treat paying clients.  Oh, and by the way, the table was dusty as were the tables on both sides of us. What were they doing getting ready to open? Clearly not paying attention to cleanliness.
This place is too good. Don't come here. It's hard enough to get reservations as it is. So please, don't come here.

Misi is fantastic. Best word to describe the entire experience. Simple and clean decor. Great service. Unbelievable pasta and appetizers. The charred peppers and ricotta are an absolute must. The cooked tomatoes were outrageously delicious and you can’t go wrong with any of the pasta dishes. Located in South Williamsburg next to Domino Park, come for a meal and walk it off along the East River!
Pasta was good. Environment as well as interior was nice. Waiter claimed there is no suck thing as pairing of wine to food, and could not recommend any wine with the ordered food.
Loved it! Great Italian food

The pastas are amazing as are the first course dishes (mostly vegetable-based). I am in love with the spinach and marscapone tortelli. The ambiance in the day is so bright and clean. Really enjoyable place. They are also stroller friendly for parents who want their fancy pasta fix in the lovely company of their offspring.
Food was excellent, waiting staff not so

The appetizers take the center stage.  Space is beautiful and convenient to the Domino Park for parents who need a child friendly spot/spacious for strollers.   The server was clueless about serving a family and didn't apologize when we were waiting 1 hour 30 minutes to get to the pasta course.  Had to take one dish to go.  We arrived when they opened.  First guests and left at 12:45pm and still no pasta.
Divine.
Sat at the bar, pastas were all incredible as well as the appetizers.  The gelato was incredibly simple yet tasteful.  4 stars because of the hour and a half wait.

Incredible pasta as you would have expected from Missy, but fell far from Lilia. Ordered 5 items off the menu, everything was good....but not great, and extremely salty. More forgivable if it were the pasta, but the Chanterelles, leeks, and peppers were way. too. salty.  Would I recommend coming here? Hard maybe. For me, I’d just stick to trying to get a seat at Lilia.

Had to book a reservation here a month in advance, but the wait was totally worth it.  To start, we got the roasted peppers with the *~FrEsHeSt~* ricotta cheese generously slathered on crostini. Yes, I’m also drooling thinking about this right now — I need more of it in my life. Even my lactose intolerant friend (with pills in tow) did not regret ordering this app  For entrees we got a safffon-clam pasta and a spinach mascarpone tortellini. 10/10 would go again for fresh pasta and amazing cheese

Delicious fresh food, essentially pasta and vegetables, but cooked to perfection! Not your traditional pasta experience and definitely worth a try! Great environment for after dinner too as you caln walk with a great view just a hundred meter away!
Perfect pasta dishes and a small assortment of starters. Tasty drinks as well.
Sublime fresh pasta, smart appealing decor, coupled with passionate but not pretentious excellent service!
Very white crowd
Best meal in New York when I was there. Definitely the best Italian I’ve had in years. It’s a must. Just go!
Ordered the sheep’s milk ricotta filled occhi w bottarga and lemon. Boldly simple. This dish reminds that cooking doesn’t have to be complicated, just enjoyable.

Last evening was our third time dining at Misi. I think I’ve finally got a handle on why I think Misi is the greatest restaurant I’ve ever dined in. Most people rate a restaurant solely on the food. I rate a restaurant on the total experience. Just like viewing a Broadway play or listening to a great symphony orchestra you are forced to take in and analyze the entire package. Misi is the entire package. From the second you walk in and before the great Aloha( we are from Hawaii) greeting you notice the soft but enjoyable sound of those on the line and the chef’s and sous chef’s constantly communicating. Then comes the honest and loving greeting. Memories of past evenings are communicated from those special ladies who are in charge of the “island” where you check in. Then, if you were smart and reserved seats at the Chef’s Counter you are privileged to be able to watch the concert/theater enfold right in front of you during the hours spent eating and watching what’s in front of you. Your first smaller courses are some of the most perfect fruits and vegetables you can imagine. They are never too fussy and always created so that you can appreciate each and every component. Textures and hues are expressionistic scenes and never too heavy. Then comes the pastas. OMG are they unbelievable. Again, never too rich or heavy but with multi levels of clean and beautiful flavors and colors. Being former wine Educators from NYC for thirty years my wife and I really appreciate the way the wine list marries the food. Many single vineyards and hard to find wines that are explained just the way we taught our wine courses. There’s absolutely no pompousness usually found in other great restaurants like Misi. Just the love and joy of something grown in the ground from Mother Nature. The whole evening is a theater of love. Just watching the non stop movements of those who were creating unusual and great things in front of us made for a very special occasion. Last night we had the Charred marinated peppers whipped ricotta crostini;  slow roasted tomatoes with hot honey, coriander , fennel seed;   lemon cucumber, fennel herbs, PASTAS:  corzetti, marinated sun gold tomatoes, garlic pecorino summer herbs; mandilli basil pesto, Sicilian almonds; Sheep’s milk ricotta filled occhi, bottarga, lemon. Oh! Fabulous gelato...strawberry and cream and our favorite expresso.
Pasta was out of this world! I don't usually like gelato, but I devoured it here. From start to finish, a delicious meal.
Food was really good. Service was slow. Plates were taken without being asked. Would eat here again, hoping for faster service.
Amazing pasta of course, appetizers are also quite good. Go early to minimize the yapping from wannabe influencers.

Amazing pastas. Super cool restaurant and ambiance. There are two huge bar seating areas which you will most likely sit at unless your party is more than 2 people in which you would get some of the few actual tables. I preferred sitting at the bar because the experience seemed more authentic. The roasted tomatoes with hot honey appetizer and the sheep’s milk ricotta filled occhi pasta are A MUST. I have a feeling that this pasta dish is the shining star compared to the other ones. The only desserts that they have are gelato which are made in house and amazingly creamy and yummy. No dairy free desserts unfortunately. Regardless, I was very impressed with the food and plan on returning soon!

Beautiful restaurant in Brooklyn. I went right as they opened so I did not have to wait, but the restaurant filled up quickly. They have a windowed room where you can watch them make all of the pasta by hand and it is quite mesmerizing. I made the mistake of ordering 1 appetizer, 1 pasta, and 1 dessert for one person. I do not regret it, but I was absolutely stuffed and I could not finish everything. I started with the grilled baby artichokes with mint salsa verde and it was incredible. The artichokes were so tender and the mint salsa verde was perfect for the summer heat. I could not finish this dish I had the hardest time deciding what pasta i wanted to try and i ended up trying the classic fettuccine with buffalo butter and parmigiano. Perfectly cooked noodles. Nice heavy butter with tons of cheese to make you feel full after one bite...but also so delicious you keep going back. I wish i was in NY for a longer period of time so i could come back to try all of the pastas here. The dessert. Goodness gracious that homemade strawberries and cream gelato...I might have to say it was better than the pasta. You just have to try it for yourself. They have a few flavors that are always on the menu and a seasonal flavor or two. This strawberries and cream was seasonal for June.  Definitely recommend this restaurant for everything they have. Great veggie appetizers, fantastic pasta, and incredible gelato.
Overpriced, food is good , but portions are tiny, they fill only 1/4 th of vine glass .
We sat at the bar and had amazing food! No-nonse Italian, made with simple ingredients. Trendy locale. Definitely a spot to check out if you're in the neighborhood and can get a reservation.

Very good pastas, as you would expect from this chef. Vegetarian friendly. All antipasto in the teens; all entrees in the twenties. We thought this was quite reasonable. Service was very good, appropriately attentive but providing plenty of space for uninterrupted conversation. Only knock is sound level.
I actually finished my plate in this restaurant. I completely recommend it for people that appreciate the art of pasta and vegetable dishes.
Best leek dish I’ve ever eaten. $35 corkage fee. That leek dish may be one of my favorite appetizers out there. Lovvvvvvved sitting in front of the kitchen.
Great atmosphere and outstanding food. Whipped ricotta crostini and spinach & mascarpone filled tortelli are a must
Very special dished. Definitely go there. Share everything!

Overall, I am pretty disappointed with my dinner at Misi. Buying into the hype, I made a reservation a month in advance (are they really this booked?). I started with the zucchini (quite tasty and simple) but the charred marinated peppers were unpalatable. I assumed that if they were charred, they would arrive hot and crispy. They were neither. They tasted like the mushy, over-marinated mess you would find in a grocery store jar of giardiniera. The pastas (particularly the tortelli) salvaged the meal. My biggest gripe with this meal was that it was a 90+ degree day and the establishment did not have any air conditioning. When eating hot, overpriced pasta that I waited a month for, I'd prefer not to be dripping in sweat. The place was unbearable and it is egregious they would take people's money when they cannot offer a basic comfort like AC during a NYC heatwave.

Tldr: Authentic handmade Italian pasta and antipasto for a very reasonable price  I went here with my wife after hearing about misi via a food channel. As opposed to how it was presented in the video, I found misi to be pretty laid back despite the modern styling and chic look of its servers.  We ordered 2 antipasto and 2 pasta dishes to share, and the total including tip was about $85, which is very reasonable for the quality of food you're getting. There's even a large glass wall that allow patrons to witness the pasta making process, which is done mostly by hand!  The pasta was simply delicious and had that perfect texture of just being chewy enough. The sauces were simple but fantastic , never overpowering the pasta. However, the star of the show would be the antipasti. We got the eggplant and artichoke and they were about $15 per dish, but each one left more of an impression on me than the pasta! They each possessed exciting flavors that blew me away.  Overall, I can definitely see myself returning to misi to try all of the antipasti dishes.

Fresh and simple.  Appetizers are vegetable based and main courses are pasta.  All pasta is fresh and you can definitely taste it. Artichokes were delicious.  Ricotta appetizer was also wonderful but very rich. Eating it with the peppers gave a great balance.  Pastas were all very good.  Stuffed pastas almost melted in your mouth. Desserts were all gelato options. The olive oil gelato was my favorite. The rest of my party didn’t care for it at all so if you don’t care for salty savory dessert it might not be for you. My only criticism was that the appetizers came out one at a time. This ended up working out fine as we all shared each one as it came out, but I think the servers should tell you this is how the apps are served.  Decor is clean and fresh. Very appealing for me.  Servers and hosts were friendly and helpful. Would highly recommend.

Misi was incredibly simple, and direct. The menu has pastas, and apps. The dessert menu presents gelatos. There is something incredibly refreshing about the brevity and directness of their menu.  They had a porterhouse special, which for the oz. was actually well priced. I wish there was a protein or two anchored on the menu for those who want to diversify from the starches, but you’re coming to Misi for pasta.  Service was decent, ambiance very crisp and minimal.

Misi's tagline is, "keep it simple" in this case, simple will not ever equal bad, because the food is delicious. The ricotta is made in house, the pasta has perfect texture, and the vegetables and divine. I never thought I would be so excited about eating peas, but here we are. Finish off you meal with gelato! And don't feel like you have to share.
Highly suggest getting the ricotta & peppers app, spinach pasta for main meal. great prices & ambiance

Maybe over-hyped, but very good. Lots of great vegetarian options. Super packed on an early Monday night, but but still very friendly and welcoming. As walk-ins, we were seated at the bar after only a 10 minute wait. Bartender was supper attentive and helped us make good choices.  Food came out quickly but we never felt rushed.  Romanesco was *amazingly* good. Charred precisely to get a perfect flavor and crunch without being burnt.  I almost want to go back and just order 3 portions of this for dinner next time!  Raw fennel salad exactly what you'd expect anywhere in NYC.  Runner beans were interesting and tasty. They are kind of flat and almost meaty tasting, but in a good way.  Chickpea pappardelle was actually just regular wheat flour pappardelle with some chickpeas on top. The sauce interesting and good with an unexpected hint of citrus.  Rigatoni was indistinguishable from what I could make at home with a box and a jar.  Pistachio gelato was very Pistachio and very good and not too sweet.  Olive oil gelato was interesting and probably worth trying once if you have enough people to spread it around, but not something I wanted to finish or to get again.
